# Commit: Changelog, docs, and version bump

See **`.cursor/rules/app-version-cadence.mdc`** for **why** the footer version does not auto-increment, and **`.cursor/rules/agent-task-version-bump.mdc`** for the **mandatory patch bump after every agent task** that commits.

## Changelog shape (no silent `[Unreleased]` dumps)

- **Every ship-ready changelog bullet must live under a dated, semver header** ŌĆö **`## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`** ŌĆö where **`X.Y.Z`** matches **root `package.json`** **after** the **`npm version patch`** for that work (same task / same push series).
- **Do not** accumulate long lists under **`## [Unreleased]`**. That section hides the version string **that** operators and Admin About rely on. If Keep a Changelog style is kept, **`[Unreleased]`** may stay **empty** or contain at most a short note that the next bump will move entries ŌĆö prefer skipping **`[Unreleased]`** entirely and writing straight into **`## [next patch] - date`** once the version is known.
- **Workflow:** bump **`package.json`** patch ŌåÆ immediately add bullets under **`## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`** with **`X.Y.Z`** equal to the new version ŌåÆ operators always see **which semver** contains **which change**.

Treat **prompt finished** / **task done** / **hand-off ready** the same as **before `git push`**: if the agent changed the tree, bump patch and add **`CHANGELOG.md`** bullets under the **matching version section** ŌĆö **not only** when the user types **commit**.

When the user says **"commit"** (or asks to commit changes), or when finishing **any shippable task** before **`git push`**:

1. **Review and update** before committing:
   - **CHANGELOG.md** ŌĆö Under **`## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`** (same **`X.Y.Z`** as bumped **`package.json`**), add **`### Added` / `Changed` / `Fixed` / `Removed`** as appropriate. Do **not** leave ship-ready notes only under **`[Unreleased]`**.
   - **README.md** ŌĆö Update if the change affects setup, usage, or documented behavior.
   - **docs/** ŌĆö Scan relevant `.md` files (e.g. deployment, payments, troubleshooting) and update any that are affected.

2. **Version bump (patch) ŌĆö default for real work:**
   - **Agents:** follow **`.cursor/rules/agent-task-version-bump.mdc`** ŌĆö bump on **every** committed task.
   - For **every user-visible or behavior-changing** contribution (API, React, mail, payments, migrations affecting runtime, etc.), bump **`package.json`** and **`package-lock.json`** at the **repository root** in the **same commit series** as the change (or the immediate follow-up commit before push). Use e.g. **`npm version patch --no-git-tag-version`**.
   - If you add **any** changelog bullet for that task, treat a **patch bump as mandatory** unless the entry is explicitly docs-only noise.
   - **`X.Y.Z` in the changelog header must equal** the bumped **`package.json`** version for that release line.

3. **Footer / prod alignment:** Storefront and admin show **`footer.version`** via **`APP_VERSION`** (**`resources/js/config/version.js`** ŌåÉ **`__APP_VERSION__`** from **`vite.config.js`**). **`config('app.version')`** reads **`package.json`** unless **`APP_VERSION`** overrides in `.env`. **Never merge to `prod` or deploy** without ensuring the integration tip includes a semver bump **after** the last user-visible change, then **`npm run build`** in CI or locally so assets embed the new number.

4. **Exceptions:** Docs-only / rule-only / task-markdown-only edits with **no** changelog runtime entry may skip a bump (if you still document the change, use a **versioned** section when you bump).

5. **If in doubt:** Bump patch ŌĆö stale footer versions confuse operators more than an extra patch digit.

6. **Branching:** Changelog and version commits belong on the **integration branch** (**`agentdevelop`** default, or **`AGENT_GIT_BRANCH`**). Promoting to **`master`** / **`prod`** follows **`.cursor/rules/git-agent-branch-workflow.mdc`**.
